snippet: Mikheil Saakashvili said he would work with the winning coalition as it forms a new government.
abstract: Pres Mikheil Saakashvili of Georgia concedes defeat in parliamentary elections and declares himself an opposition politician, extraordinary event in a country whose other post-Soviet leaders have typically had to be forced from office; Saakashvili will remain president until 2013 and will have to serve alongside Bidzinia Ivanishvili, his challenger, who will likely be prime minister; partnership will be difficult given men's ideological differences.
lead_paragraph: Mikheil Saakashvili said he would work with the winning coalition as it forms a new government.

headline.seo: Georgia’s President Concedes Defeat in Parliamentary Election

headline.print_headline: Georgia’s President, in an Extraordinary Turn, Concedes an Election Defeat
